--[[
World chat content, faction-gated AND typed (tagged authoring format).
Each faction pool (shared / alliance / horde) has three lists you can extend freely:
  lines  = standalone one-liners            -> spoken by a single character
  duos   = two-person back-and-forth        -> two fixed speakers alternate A / B / A / B
  groups = group discussions / list threads -> a rotating cast of 4-6 voices, one line each
  shared = broadcast to EVERYONE (voiced by Alliance characters); alliance/horde = that faction only.

TAGGED AUTHORING FORMAT (string-first; back-compatible)
-------------------------------------------------------
A `lines` entry is EITHER a bare string (untagged = a universal/global wildcard,
fit for any character in any area) OR a table whose [1] is the text and whose
named keys are metadata:
  { "text", roles={...}, moods={...}, areas=<list|map>, weight=<n>, cooldown=<n> }

A `duos`/`groups` entry is a table with `chain={...}` (the ordered lines) plus the
same optional tags:
  { chain={"line A", "line B"}, roles={...}, moods={...}, areas=<...> }
(Legacy bare {"a","b"} arrays still parse as untagged chains, but new content
should use chain= form.)

Tag fields (ALL optional; omit to stay global/universal):
  roles  -- list of role archetypes this line suits. Omit = any role.
            guard citizen vendor innkeeper adventurer soldier mage priest
            craftsman farmer sailor noble drunkard urchin
  moods  -- list of personalities this line suits. Omit = any personality.
            warm gruff cheerful weary wry boastful nervous solemn greedy
            kindly bitter dreamy brave cowardly gossipy
  areas  -- area fit. Three forms:
            * OMITTED      -> global, fits any area.
            * LIST  {"city","rural"}          -> uniform weight across those areas.
            * MAP   {battlefield=3, rural=1}  -> graded likelihood; areas NOT
              listed are HARD-EXCLUDED (the line never fires there).
            Valid areas: city rural battlefield coast wilderness road
  weight   -- relative pick frequency (default 1). Bump nice generic lines up.
  cooldown -- min ticks before this exact line repeats (default from config).
              Raise for especially distinctive lines so they don't recur fast.

Examples:
  "The lamplighters are making their rounds.",                 -- global wildcard
  { "Three coppers a loaf and not a copper less.",
    roles={"vendor"}, moods={"gruff","greedy"}, areas={"city"} },
  { "Orcs in the treeline -- to arms!", roles={"soldier","guard"},
    moods={"nervous","brave"}, areas={battlefield=3, rural=1} },   -- graded, never in city

IMPORTANT: leave genuinely generic ambience UNTAGGED and global on purpose. That
is the universal fallback pool the matcher needs so no character ever goes
silent. Tag a line only when its content clearly implies a role/mood/area.

Placeholders work in any line. Core: %zone% %instance% %class% %bg%.
World/flavor: %profession% %activity% %city% %race% %monster% %critter% %boss%
%consumable% %item% %rep% %mount% %spell% %rare% %pvptitle% %title% %emote%
%event% %season% %timeofday% %weather% %shop% %route% %tale% %npc% %currency%
%food% %drink% %tradegood% %companion% %enchant% %toy% %herb% %ore% %gem% %fish%.
Discouraged (player-imitation; see Tone below): %role% %difficulty% %gearscore%.
See README.md or the pools near the top of npcTalk.lua for the full list.

Tone: in-world roleplay chatter spoken by CIVILIANS, GUARDS, VENDORS, and the
occasional road-weary adventurer talking about life in Azeroth. These are NPCs,
NOT an imitation of real players. Do NOT write lines that emulate player
behaviour: no LFG/LFM, no "anyone wanna group?", no gearscore/parse talk, no
auction-house adverts, no raid logistics. Talk about the world, the weather, the
gossip, the work, the rumors -- the texture of a living city -- not about
queueing for content. Keep it grounded in the lore: no real-world references, no
out-of-character meta, no fourth-wall jokes. Humor is welcome, but it should be
the kind a tavern regular would tell, not a forum poster.
]]--

